msgstr ""

#: .uk.WINSLOW_MAP_FORLORNWRECKAGE_SUBTITLE
msgid "Lost Remnant of the UES 'Contact Light'"
msgstr ""

#: .uk.WINSLOW_MAP_FORLORNWRECKAGE_BAZAAR_SEER
msgid ""
"<style=cWorldEvent>You dream of an eternal cold, and shattered glass...</"
"style>"
msgstr ""

#: .uk.WINSLOW_MAP_FORLORNWRECKAGE_LORE
msgid ""
"<style=cMono>Welcome to the DataScraper (v3.1.54 – modded branch)\n"
"$ Scraping memory... done.\n"
"$ Resolving... done.\n"
"$ Combing for relevant data... done.\n"
"$ Scraping modded initials... done.\n"
"Outputting local audio transcriptions...\n"
"</style>\n"
"\n"
"<style=cMono>Day 5</style>\n"
"<style=cMono>$ Begin Transmission</style>\n"
"We located the remaining parts of the Contact Light... James went "
"*somewhere* he told me that he'd come back so I setup camp at one of the "
"wrecks, I'd make a report to Safe Travels buuuut my transmitter got "
"absolutely decimated by an encounter we had in a valley.. Oh! James is back "
"okay can yo-\n"
"<style=cMono>$ Transmission Ended</style>\n"
"\n"
"<style=cMono>Day 6</style>\n"
"<style=cMono>$ Begin Transmission</style>\n"
"Okay- so James and I got roughed up bad. We moved our camp behind one of the "
"Cargo holds, we did sent a signal message to Safe Travels 4 days ago but we "
"have not gotten a response since.. all we got ever since we sent it is "
"garbled up noise with the occasional faint voices. The most clear thing we "
"heard was something about a distress signal and... love? I don't know but "
"while going through the cargo holds I found this old journal book thingy, "
"it's very hard to read though due to the amount of time it spent here... "
"I'll try to decypher what it says though, looks interesting.\n"
"<style=cMono>$ Transmission Ended</style>\n"
"\n"
"<style=cMono>Day 8</style>\n"
"<style=cMono>$ Begin Transmission</style>\n"
"Alright so about the journal, I managed to decypher most of it and I believe "
"it's about that massive structure in-front of the mountain in the distance? "
"Let me read a part of it. “This bridge just goes on forever... but at least "
"it is a bridge. Between this blizzard and the mountain fog I can't see more "
"than two meters ahead, even with my mounted lights.“ Yeesh. That guy must "
"have been unlucky... Anyway there are some nice photos of these creatures, "
"some even I haven't seen before! Thank god! There's like a photo of this "
"fire-y beast..? Looks like something straight out of mythology...\n"
"<style=cMono>$ Transmission Ended</style>\n"
"\n"
"<style=cMono>Local text transcriptions complete.\n"
"</style>"
msgstr ""

